{"questionId":"26591","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A polygraph test is used to determine whether people are telling the truth or not, but it is not&nbsp;completely accurate. When a person tells the truth, they have a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>%</mo></math> chance of failing the test.&nbsp;Each test outcome is independent of any previous test outcome.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> people take a polygraph test and all <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> tell the truth.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the probability that exactly <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math> people will fail this polygraph test.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition of binomial probability&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0881</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0880803</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26591","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ2.5b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the probability that exactly 4 people will fail this polygraph test.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.5—Probability concepts, expected numbers","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}